article.headline: IPFW 71, Centenary 59
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. -- Ben Botts scored 17 and IPFW scored 23 points off the bench as the Mastodons beat Centenary 71-59 Thursday night in the Summit League. David Carson and Jakari Johnson scored 12 each for IPFW (9-14, 4-8), which shot 47 percent from the field and 8-of-17 from three-point range. Nick Stallings had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Gents (7-16, 5-6), who shot just 33 percent overall. Gary Redus had 13 and Chase Adams 10. Both teams shot 19-of-25 from the free-throw line. IPFW led 32-27 at the break. The Gents tied twice early in the second half, but the Mastodons went on a 15-2 run to gain a 13-point edge with 1:22 left, their largest lead of the game. Centenary outrebounded IPFW 35-31.
